@sanjoy Thanks for your help very much.
According to speech at TensorFlow Dev Summit 2017(https://youtu.be/kAOanJczHA0?t=2831),
Code size can be evaluated by Original(Runtime + Graph) compare with Compiled(Code+Weigh).
As I know, Graph = TF graph, what does the rumtime means? Does it mean all libraries that graph need to use?
And does Code+Weight mean the binary file which compiled by AOT?
